(13, 'VIRBANT HO CHI MINH CITY', 'Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text.', '<div>Located in the South of Vietnam, Ho Chi Minh City (HCMC), &nbsp;<br />\r\nis the largest and most important cities inVietnam in annual GDP. The city alone of 8.2million people (9% of total population) accounts for 22% of the countries GDP. This city is not only a centre of commerce and finance, but also Vietnam&rsquo;s hu for science, culture, education and technology. With a growing middle class, HCMC has enormous market potential. The city boasts the best infrastructure in the nation including modern transportation and telecommunication systems to create modern well-planned city that can become one of the most desirable and international business centre in Southeast Asia.</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 450, '2016-12-11 12:20:34', '2016-12-11 15:38:07', 'true', '/data/image/img2.jpg', 'virbant-ho-chi-minh-city', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(14, 'RENTAL YIELDS', 'There are many variations of passages of Lorem Ipsum available, but the majority have suffered alteration in some form, by injected humour, or randomised words which don''t look even slightly believable.', '<div style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<div><strong>With the increasing inflow of foreign investment, more expatriates and local professionals are expected to relocate to Vietnam&rsquo;s major cities, which promises good rental yields for homeowners</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Affordability</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>High-end residential options with a<br />\r\nfull suite of complimentary facilities, good location,<br />\r\nand convenient accessibility are very affordable,<br />\r\ncompared to its regional peers.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Capital Appreciation</strong><br />\r\n​The property market&rsquo;s<br />\r\nlong term growth is highly potential, driven by the<br />\r\ncountry&rsquo;s stable political environment, promising<br />\r\neconomy, high urbanisation rate and young<br />\r\npopulation</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Tourism paradise.</strong><br />\r\nA popular tourist destination with major ASEAN cities located within a 2-hour flight, Vietnam is an ideal place for vacationers and<br />\r\nretirees</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 450, '2016-12-11 12:21:31', '2016-12-11 15:39:47', 'true', '/data/image/img1.jpg', 'rental-yields', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(15, 'Your Funding Needs', 'updating', '<div>Having been investing in Vietnam for over 5 years, LinkedProperties can help you navigate through your funding requirements.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Did you know that there are already many Australian and International banks already established in Vietnam. This is testament to the growth and confidence the wider global business community have of the country.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>This makes Vietnam a much easier and assured investment opportunity for Australians.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>1. Unlike investing in other countries where 100% cash is required, all you need to invest is a minimum 30% deposit.<br />\r\n2. LinkedProperties can help you obtain a loan pre-approval before you even set foot in Vietnam<br />\r\n3. So once you arrive, you have your funding sorted, leaving you to do the viewing and inspections.<br />\r\n4. This investment environment for the hardened investor obviously has its strategic advantages whereby you can use gearing to expand your portfolio.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Dealing with brands you can trust and are comfortable back at home makes investing a much more assured and pleasant experience. As they operate with a similar customer service, professionalism and values as back at home, you will find it reduces bureaucracy and you are in control of what is happening every step of the way.</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 454, '2016-12-11 15:29:13', '2016-12-11 15:35:46', 'true', '/data/image/img2.jpg', 'your-funding-needs', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(16, 'Investment Question And Anwerered', 'updating', '<div>\r\n<div><strong>1. WHO CAN BUY? </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>Individuals - all foreigners who are granted a visa to Vietnam are allowed to buy residential properties in the country.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>2. TYPES OF PROPERTY</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>All types of residential sector properties including condominiums and landed property such as villa and townhouses within a development project.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>3. NUMBER OF PROPERTIES</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>There is no limit on the number of units a foreigner can buy, but the total number of dwelling units owned by foreigners must not exceed 30% of the total units in one condominium complex, or not exceed 10% of landed property within a development project.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>4. PURPOSE OF PURCHASE</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>The properties owned by foreigners can be sub-leased, inherited and collateralized (previously only for owner occupying purpose and not to be rented out).</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 453, '2016-12-11 15:32:52', '2016-12-11 15:36:36', 'true', '/data/image/img1.jpg', 'investment-question-and-anwerered', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(17, 'Investment Question And Anwerered', 'updating', '<div><strong>5. THE LENGTH OF TENURE</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>The tenure allowed to foreign individuals buying homes is a 50-year leasehold with renewal possibility upon expiration, which remains unchanged. Foreign individuals married to Vietnamese citizens are entitled to freehold tenure. For a foreigner selling to a Vietnamese citizen, the tenure will convert to Freehold.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Vietnam is not an investment for everyone, but those who have said &lsquo;I wish I&rsquo;d invested in China, Thailand, Singapore or Jakarta all those years ago&rsquo; will jump at the chance of getting in at the start!</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>DW - Add taxation costs.&nbsp;<br />\r\nVAT<br />\r\nReg Fees<br />\r\nReg of title<br />\r\nNotarys Fees</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 453, '2016-12-11 15:34:35', '2016-12-11 15:37:31', 'true', '/data/image/img2.jpg', 'investment-question-and-anwerered', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(18, 'HO-CHI-MINH CITY', 'HO-CHI-MINH CITY', 'Vietnam is located in South-East Asia. Vietnam is bordered by China in the North, Loas on the west and Cambodia on the South-West. Across to the right is the South China Sea &ndash; in parallel with the Philippines. Further down from the South-West is the Gulf of Thailand and the country of Malaysia.<br />\r\nYou could say Vietnam is strategically located among 4 of the most high-tech industrialized countries of the last few decades &ndash; being Hong Kong, Singapore, Taiwan and lastly Korea.<br />\r\n&nbsp;Vietnam itself is named as one of the &lsquo;5 Tiger Cub Economies&rsquo;, along with Malaysia, Indonesia, Philippines and Thailand. Renowned financial experts from HSBC and Goldman Sachs have commented that these up and coming rising tigers follow the same export driven economic models of economic development that is similar to the success of the Four Asian Tigers. Vietnam is included in Goldman Sachs, next Eleven for its potential for rapid growth and large, young population to drive this growth, as well as HSBC&rsquo;s top 50 economies for strong continuous growth for 2050.', NULL, 'investment', 451, '2016-12-11 15:41:25', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/img1.jpg', 'ho-chi-minh-city', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(19, 'CITY AND THE UTILITIES', 'CITY AND THE UTILITIES', '<div><strong>HCMC</strong><br />\r\nHo Chi Minh City (HCMC) is the largest city in Vietnam and with its fast pace and rapid growth, is starting to resemble the commercial hub of the country.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Ports</strong><br />\r\nSaigon Port is a network of ports in Ho Chi Minh City mainly along Saigon River. It serves as a gateway to the Mekong River Delta, the South China Sea (83 km away from the sea) and the Asia continent.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Airport</strong><br />\r\nHCMC is served by Ton Son Nhat International Airport located North-West of HCMC &ndash; 7km from the HCMC Centre. (20-30mins)<br />\r\nThe new airport approved in 2014 Long Thanh International Airport (LTIA) &nbsp;is proposed to be built in Long Thanh, Dong Nai Province, located in Southern Vietnam, approximately 45km north-east of HCMC.</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 451, '2016-12-11 15:42:35', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/6.jpg', 'city-and-the-utilities', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(20, 'THE DISTRICT', 'THE DISTRICT', '<div><strong>District 1</strong><br />\r\nD1 is the centre of Vietnam. This is where you will find all financial, commercial and administrative activity. the global businesses located such as HSBC, Samsung, Intel Corp, Deloitte, to the world famous hotels like Intercontinental, Hyatt to Designer retail including Channel, Gucci, Louis Vuitton, Prada. &nbsp;Restaurants and shops offering cuisines and goods from around the world are found alongside expensive, upscale hotels. This district has felt the effects of globalisation and development most heavily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>District 2</strong><br />\r\nDistrict 2 is home to many long-term expats who want living standards close to that of their home countries. While this district is close to the city centre, it&#39;s still far enough away to be secluded from District 1&#39;s endless activity. District 2 (specifically Thao Dien Ward and An Phu Ward) is an alluring family-friendly settlement for Western expats and wealthy Vietnamese as it provides a high standard of living. These two wards offer less chaotic streets, numerous international schools, and Westernised housing options.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Thao Dien and An Phu both have high-quality residential apartments, large houses and villas &ndash; some with pools and in walled compounds &ndash; at reasonable prices. Numerous restaurants, retail shops, grocery stores and commercial offices can be found lining the streets here.<br />\r\nMany foreign universities are located here including; American International School (USA), Singapore International School (Singapore), British and Australian International School.</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>District 7</strong><br />\r\nSimilar to District 2, many expats living in Ho Chi Minh City choose to make District 7 their home. The district is filled with wide, tree-lined streets surrounded by high-quality apartment buildings and villas for long-term residents. There is little development outside of housing accommodation, so it is a perfect spot to enjoy personal space as well as extensive greenery.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Phu My Hung is the most popular area of District 7, catering to expats with international schools, swimming pools, Western grocery stores and an increasing number of restaurants and shops.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Do not expect much in terms of nightlife activities or street life. The allure of District 7 is its peaceful, quiet atmosphere. Designed with a wealthy, high-income population in mind, houses here are more expensive than other areas of the city.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>District 7 is quite remote from the city centre, with commute times at around 40 minutes and less convenient public transportation options. While it is nowhere close to a true Vietnamese experience, District 7 offers a peaceful lifestyle for families away from the noise and chaos of the city.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 451, '2016-12-11 15:45:37', '2016-12-11 15:47:01', 'true', '/data/image/blog/skyline-louisville-downtown.jpg', 'the-district', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(21, 'KEY DEMOGRAPHICS OF HCMC', 'KEY DEMOGRAPHICS OF HCMC', 'Key Demographics of HCMC\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Region: Southern Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>Population: 8,2 million</li>\r\n	<li>Gross City Production: USD $ 36 billion (2013)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Force: 4.7 million (2012)</li>\r\n	<li>Latest Unemployment Rate: 4.83% (2013)</li>\r\n	<li>Per Capita Personal Income: $4,500</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative units: 24 districts (rural, suburban and urban)Vietnam is located in South-East Asia. Vietnam is bordered by China in the North, Loas on the west and Cambodia on the South-West. Across to the right is the South China Sea &ndash; in parallel with the Philippines. Further down from the South-West is the Gulf of Thailand and the country of Malaysia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 451, '2016-12-11 15:46:41', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/blog/paris.jpg', 'key-demographics-of-hcmc', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(22, 'About Investing in Vietnam', 'About\r\nInvesting in Vietnam', '<div>Post 1990, Vietnam&rsquo;s has been growing at a rapid pace - GDP per capita &nbsp;averaged 6.4% a year in the 2000s. Latest figures from the WorldBank shows Vietnam continued to strengthen in 2015, with an estimated GDP growth rate of 6.7 percent. This speed of growth and expansion is a trend similar to the mighty rise of China. As history shows, the rise of a country&#39;s GDP reflects the expansion and job creation for the people of the country. This is the most exciting time, for the local and for investors - for when a country transitions from being one of the poorest, to a lower middle income country and beyond.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Just look at China, barely 20 years ago China was an agricultural country, and now they have become the second highest GDP country in the world. The wealth of the Chinese can be seen in the spending power in all the luxurious shops from Sydney to Paris to London! Not to mention their competitive appetite for apartments and investments abroad which everyone, especially if you are an astute investor over everyone has taken notice of. Now the same trend is happening in Vietnam.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Vietnam&rsquo;s economic activity moderated in the first 9 months of 2016, with GDP expanding by 6%, compared to 6.5% percent over the same period in 2015 (source JLL Q3 Vietnam Report). This growth is still much more impressive compared to established developed countries such as UK, America or Europe, who continue to struggle around 1-2% GDP. &nbsp;</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 452, '2016-12-11 15:50:47', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/img1.jpg', 'about-investing-in-vietnam', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(23, 'The key facts for Vietnam', 'The key facts for Vietnam', '<div><strong>Population</strong><br />\r\n91.70 million</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>GDP</strong><br />\r\n$193.6 billion</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>GDP growth</strong><br />\r\n6.7%</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Inflation</strong><br />\r\n0.6%</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Source - WorldBank 2015</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 452, '2016-12-11 15:51:32', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/img2.jpg', 'the-key-facts-for-vietnam', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(24, 'VIETNAM PROPERTY MANAGEMENT', 'PROPERTY MANAGEMENT', '<div>HCMC has been consistently achieving 6-8% gross yield for the last 5 years. As shown under Economy[hyperlink to page] - the continuous &nbsp;growth in GDP has positively transpired through to the property market. Not only is yield much higher than in Australia of c3-3.5%, the gain in property value has favorably been in the circa 8-12% per year.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>With the expertise of the architects and agents we work with, they can advise you on the best proposition for designing and fitting out your investment property, to keep costs low and maximise returns.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>We at LinkedProperties work with rental agents to help you rent out and manage your property from the moment it is ready. As we provide an end to end service, we will be helping you to find prospective tenants even before it is handed over to you. This will reduce any loss of rental.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>We save you the hassle, stress and time to even need to be in the country to find tenants and manage any issues that may arise.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>You can safely leave the handling of the post purchase to our team, with your express agreement, sit back and wait for the monthly rental income will be deposited into your bank account.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n', NULL, 'investment', 455, '2016-12-11 15:54:20', NULL, 'true', '/data/image/img1.jpg', 'vietnam-property-management', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(25, 'We are a team based out of Sydney and HCMC.', 'We are a team based out of Sydney and HCMC.', '<div style="text-align: justify;">When it comes to realizing your investment potential, we can accommodate to meeting with you in Australia to go through the possibilities available.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">We showcase and share our experiences and give you up to date information on where the market is heading.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">We can work out a schedule to best meet your investment needs and guide you through the course of the process.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Surprisingly, for a purchase such as &#39;off the plan&#39; apartments this can be commenced no more than a 1 week visit in HCMC. &nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Our services includes doing all the hard-work for you, so that you don&#39;t have to!</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">As personal investors having &#39;put our money where our mouth is&#39; and the many years of first hand experience of being involved in the purchasing process, we aim to &nbsp;make your investment as seamless and time efficient as possible.</div>\r\n', NULL, 'service', 469, '2016-12-11 16:37:30', '2016-12-11 17:01:09', 'true', '/data/image/5.jpg', 'we-are-a-team-based-out-of-sydney-and-hcmc', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương'),
(26, 'Our main services include', 'Our main services include', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Identifying the opportunities available to suit your budget</li>\r\n	<li>Putting together a viewing itinerary who respective property agents including travel arrangements and English speaking agents</li>\r\n	<li>Help you open a bank account in Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>Help you obtain funding, as if you were buying an investment property in Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Introduce you to solicitors (if required) to help with the purchase</li>\r\n	<li>Put you in touch with architects and builders if you are buying &nbsp;&#39;&oacute;ff the plan&#39;</li>\r\n	<li>Take care of your rental needs once the property is yours and ready to earn you rental income.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, 'service', 469, '2016-12-11 16:38:00', '2016-12-11 16:59:35', 'true', '/data/image/8.jpg', 'our-main-services-include', 'false', '', 'Trường Khương');
